{
  "texts": [
    "With its bit-level fine-grained customized structure, parallel computing ability, and efficient energy consumption, FPGAs exhibit unique advantages in deep learning applications.",
    "Using FPGAs for reservoir computing is also advantageous, as sparse connections in the reservoir model allow for simple routing techniques that match FPGA requirements.",
    "Currently, several FPGA methods have been proposed [70] [71] [72].",
    "In addition, considering the high programming requirements of FPGAs, people have proposed the implementation of RC algorithm using Application Specific Integrated Circuits (ASICs) 73, which can help improve chip performance and power consumption ratio.",
    "The disadvantage of ASICbased RC is that circuit design customization leads to relatively long development cycles, inability to scale, and high costs."
  ]
}